  • Method Details

    • addIfAbsent

      default boolean addIfAbsent(E item)
      Adds the given item to the collection only if it is not already present.

      Equality is determined by Object.equals(Object).

      Parameters:
      item - the element to add
      Returns:
      true if the item was not already contained in the collection and has been added, false otherwise

    • addIfAbsentByIdentity

      default boolean addIfAbsentByIdentity(E item)
      Adds the given element to the collection only if no identical (==) element is already present.

      Identity comparison (==) is used instead of Object.equals(Object).

      Parameters:
      item - the element to add
      Returns:
      true if the collection did not already contain the given element by identity and it was added; false otherwise
